title: Taylor Swift has a message for her fans: Vote early
Overcrowded, overpriced and overwhelmed. The UK's Covid-19 staycation nightmare
description: Beaches strewn with waste, wild campers destroying fragile habitats, warnings from an increasingly overstretched Coastguard, unaffordable accommodations. What was supposed to have been a Great British summer has, for many, become a staycation nightmare.

title: Did Fortnite just kill the App Store as we know it?
description: Fortnite maker Epic Games sent shockwaves through the tech industry this week when it sued Apple and Google, claiming both companies' app stores are monopolies. If Epic were to win the lawsuits, Apple and Google could be required to overhaul their businesses by making their app stores more favorable to developers.

title: Jared Kushner asked about 'birther' attack on Kamala Harris
description: CNN's Christiane Amanpour talks to Jared Kushner about Trump and the recent birtherism attack on presumptive Democratic vice presidential nominee Kamala Harris.

title: Lyon stun Manchester City to reach Champions League semifinals
description: Lyon stunned Manchester City on Saturday to qualify for the semifinals of the Champions League, winning 3-1.

title: Trump says snapback sanctions against Iran could come next week
description: President Donald Trump said snapback sanctions against Iran could happen as soon as next week after the UN Security Council rejected a US proposal to extend the conventional weapons embargo on Friday.

title: Vaccines are safe. But many around the world say they wouldn't take a Covid jab
description: Susan Bailey, a 57-year-old retired nurse from Florida, has had all her jabs and gets a flu shot every year. She's a vocal Joe Biden supporter -- and one of a growing number of people globally who say they wouldn't take a coronavirus vaccine even if one becomes available soon.

title: 'Clueless' is getting series reboot with a twist
description: "Clueless" is coming back, and this time, the spotlight is on Dionne Davenport.

title: India cricket legend MS Dhoni announces retirement
description: India cricket legend MS Dhoni announced his retirement from international competition on Saturday, marking the end to his 16-year career with the India National Team.

title: Brazil's Christ the Redeemer statue and Sugarloaf Mountain reopen Saturday
description: Two of Brazil's best known tourist attractions -- the Christ the Redeemer statue and Sugarloaf Mountain -- have reopened after being shut for five months due to the coronavirus pandemic.

title: Ryan Reynolds asks young people to stop 'dangerous' partying during pandemic
description: Ryan Reynolds has one simple request for young Canadians in British Columbia: Please don't kill his mom.

title: Barca star insists: The club needs change
description: After losing 3-0 to Roma in 2018, Barcelona fans might've thought it was the club's lowest ebb. After losing 4-0 to Liverpool in 2019, they might've thought it was actually the club's lowest point.

title: How these images changed a woman's family history
description: Her uncle's decision to fight in World War II horrified his conservative Mennonite family, who rarely spoke of him even after his death. She discovers the truth about his service decades later.

title: Pandemic power play: It's China vs. US in Latin America
description: At first glance, the picture China's ambassador to Barbados tweeted on July 23 shows nothing more than an online meeting — a typical, screen-based representation of what life has become during the pandemic.

title: Faulty election mailers create confusion
description: Mailers meant to help voters with the absentee voting process amid the ongoing pandemic are instead sowing confusion for voters and leading some officials to levy allegations of attempted voter suppression ahead of the November election.

title: The Man Utd teenager who is a superstar in the making
description: There was a period during the winter of 2008 when every Saturday night Paul Newsham's Yorkshire home would sound like old telephone exchange switch room.

title: British tourists rush back from France to avoid quarantine
description: Thousands of British holidaymakers have been trying to return home from France in an attempt to avoid new quarantine restrictions imposed by the UK government.

title: Taiwan risks being caught up in the power struggle between the United States and China
description: It took less than 24 hours after United States Secretary of Health and Human Services Alex Azar touched down in Taiwan, in an historic visit intended to convey President Donald Trump's support for the democratic island, for China to deliver its own message.

title: A 12-year-old girl was caught on camera gambling at an Australian casino
description: A 12-year-old girl was among three minors caught gambling at a casino in Sydney, Australia, regulators said Saturday.

title: Clerk had whole paycheck stolen, officers stepped in to help
description: Arizona officers chipped in to help a clerk whose purse carrying her entire pay check was stolen. CNN's Miguel Marquez reports.

title: Trump orders TikTok's Chinese-owned parent company to divest interest in US operations
description: President Donald Trump issued an executive order Friday evening directing ByteDance, the Chinese-owned parent company of TikTok, to divest interest in the app's US operations within the next 90 days.

title: The US-China fight began with trade. Now it's the one thing still working for them
description: Tensions between the United States and China have soared as the two superpowers fight over everything from the coronavirus pandemic, human rights and Hong Kong, to who controls the technologies of the future.

title: Chef José Andrés helps feed people in Beirut after deadly explosion
description: Anderson Cooper talks with Chef José Andrés, who is in Beirut with World Central Kitchen helping feed people after the deadly explosion.  Anderson Cooper Full Circle airs Monday, Tuesday and Friday at 6p E.T.
